Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}; pat very dry with paper towels. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and @water{3/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss chickpeas on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil and half the @Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning Blend{7.2%g} (you'll use the rest later).

On a separate baking sheet, toss carrots and @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} with a large drizzle of oil and @celery salt{1%teaspoon}.

Roast chickpeas on top rack and veggies on middle rack until chickpeas are crispy and veggies are tender and browned, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: It's natural for the chickpeas to pop a bit when they roast.

Meanwhile, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine shallot, half the @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, a splash of @water{} and a pinch of @salt{}. (For 4 servings, use all the vinegar and 1/2 tsp sugar.) Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{1%minute}.

Halve, pit, and peel @avocado{1}; thinly slice. Sprinkle with @salt{}.

When chickpeas have a few minutes left, place @butter{1%tablespoon} in a second small microwave-safe bowl; microwave until melted, ~{45%seconds}. Stir in remaining Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning.

Once chickpeas are done, remove sheet from oven and pour Buffalo mixture on top; carefully toss on sheet until thoroughly coated.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}; top with chickpeas, veggies, avocado, and pickled shallot (draining first). Drizzle with @ranch dressing{3%ounce} and serve.